---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Common Bingo Prefixes in Scrabble — Front-Loading Wins"
  description="The most productive bingo prefixes in Scrabble: RE-, UN-, OUT-, OVER-, PRE-, MIS-, DIS-. Learn which beginnings produce the most 7-letter words and how to use them."
  keywords="scrabble bingo prefixes, RE words scrabble, UN prefix bingo, common prefixes scrabble, OUT words bingo, scrabble prefix strategy"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Common Bingo Prefixes in Scrabble — Front-Loading Wins",
    "description": "The most productive bingo prefixes in Scrabble: RE-, UN-, OUT-, OVER-, PRE-, MIS-, DIS-. Learn which beginnings produce the most 7-letter words.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/common-bingo-prefixes" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the best prefixes for Scrabble bingos?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "RE- is the most productive bingo prefix, creating hundreds of valid 7-letter words (READING, RELATED, REMOVED, REPAIRS). UN- is second (UNDOING, UNKNOWN, UNLOCKS). OUT-, OVER-, and PRE- round out the top 5. These 5 prefixes account for roughly 20% of all bingos played." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do prefixes help find bingos in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "When you spot a prefix on your rack (like RE), set those letters aside and check if the remaining 5 tiles form a valid base word. RE + PAINT = REPAINT (7 letters, bingo). This reduces a 7-letter search to a 5-letter one." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Can you combine prefixes and suffixes for bingos?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. RE + DO + ING = REDOING. UN + PACK + ED = UNPACKED (8 letters with board tile). Many bingos layer a prefix onto a suffixed root. With only 7 tiles, prefix + root + suffix often requires borrowing letters from the board." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Bingo Topics</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Common Bingo Prefixes in Scrabble — Front-Loading Wins</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>7 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        While most players instinctively check for suffixes (-ING, -ED), the front end of words is equally productive for bingos. Prefixes like RE-, UN-, and OUT- attach to hundreds of base words to create valid 7-letter plays. The advantage of prefix-hunting: opponents rarely block the beginning of words, making prefix bingos easier to place on crowded boards.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">The Top 7 Bingo Prefixes — Ranked</h2>

      <p>These prefixes produce the most valid 7+ letter words in competitive Scrabble, ranked by productivity.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Rank</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Prefix</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Tiles</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Root Left</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Examples</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">RE-</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">READING, REPAINT, RELATED</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">UN-</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">UNDOING, UNLOCKS, UNKNOWN</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">OUT-</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">OUTSIDE, OUTLAWS, OUTPLAY</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">OVER-</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">OVERLAY, OVERDUE, OVERTIP</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">PRE-</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">PREVIEW, PRETEND, PREVENT</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">MIS-</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">MISTAKE, MISREAD, MISLEAD</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-amber-400 font-bold">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-bold">DIS-</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-green-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">DISPLAY, DISPOSE, DISCARD</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">~20%</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Bingos use a prefix</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">RE-</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Most productive</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2 tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">RE- and UN- cost</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">RE- and UN- — The Two-Tile Powerhouses</h2>

      <p>RE- and UN- are the most efficient prefixes because they consume only 2 tiles, leaving 5 for the base word. More remaining tiles means exponentially more word possibilities.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">RE- (Repetition)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Means "again" or "back." REPAINT, READING, RELATED, REMOVED, REPAIRS, RETURNS, REBUILD. Almost any 5-letter verb can take RE- to form a bingo.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">UN- (Negation)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Means "not" or "reverse." UNDOING, UNLOCKS, UNKNOWN, UNFOLDS, UNWINDS, UNCLEAN, UNUSUAL. Works with adjectives and verbs alike.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 The RE- Advantage</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">RE- is arguably the strongest prefix because <span class="text-white font-medium">R and E are two of the most common tiles</span> (6 R's, 12 E's in the bag). You'll frequently hold both without trying. When you do, immediately check: "Can my other 5 tiles form a word that takes RE- in front?"</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Three-Tile Prefixes: OUT-, PRE-, MIS-, DIS-</h2>

      <p>These use 3 tiles, leaving 4 for the base word. Slightly less flexible than RE-/UN- but still highly productive because they attach to common English roots.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">OUT- (Exceeding)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">OUTPLAY, OUTLAWS, OUTSIDE, OUTRANK, OUTWITS. Means "surpassing" or "external." Common 4-letter roots: PLAY, LAWS, SIDE, RANK.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">PRE- (Before)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">PREVIEW, PRETEND, PREVENT, PREPARE, PREDICT. Means "before." Common roots: VIEW, TEND, VENT, PARE.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">MIS- (Wrong)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MISTAKE, MISREAD, MISLEAD, MISFIRE, MISPLAY. Means "wrong" or "badly." Almost any verb can be MIS- prefixed.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">DIS- (Opposite)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">DISPLAY, DISPOSE, DISCARD, DISCUSS, DISTURB. Means "not" or "apart." Pairs with many 4-letter roots cleanly.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">OVER- — The Long Prefix</h2>

      <p>OVER- uses 4 tiles, leaving only 3 for the base word. It's restrictive but produces overlooked bingos that opponents rarely block.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 OVER- Bingo Patterns</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">OVER + 3 letters:</span> DUE (OVERDUE), LAY (OVERLAY), TIP (OVERTIP), RAN (OVERRAN), JOY (OVERJOY)</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Board-assisted:</span> If a 4+ letter word exists on the board, play OVER in front using all 7 tiles. OVER + POWER = OVERPOWER (9 letters, still a bingo).</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">Only check when obvious:</span> Don't spend time on OVER- unless you actually hold O, V, E, R together. The 4-tile cost makes it low-probability compared to RE- or UN-.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Prefixes vs. Suffixes — When to Check Each</h2>

      <p>The speed-search method checks suffixes first because they're more productive overall. But prefixes have a unique advantage on crowded boards.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Check Prefixes When</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">No -ING, -ED, -ERS on your rack. Board endings are blocked. You hold R+E or U+N prominently. Open space exists before existing words.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Skip Prefixes When</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">You already found a suffix bingo. You don't hold R, E, U, N, O, or P. Time is running low — suffixes are faster to check.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 The Prefix Placement Advantage</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Opponents typically block word ENDINGS near premium squares. They rarely think about the space <span class="text-white font-medium">before</span> existing words. Prefix bingos often find open lanes that suffix bingos can't reach — giving you board access others miss.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Check RE- whenever you hold R+E:</span> With 6 R's and 12 E's in the bag, you'll hold both together frequently. Every time you do, spend 10 seconds checking if your other 5 tiles form a word. This habit alone finds 2-3 extra bingos per tournament.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">UN- loves adjectives and verbs:</span> UNCLEAN, UNUSUAL, UNFOLDS, UNLOCKS, UNWINDS. When you hold U+N, think of 5-letter adjectives or verbs that can be negated. Rich vein of bingos.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">OUT- for competitive verbs:</span> OUTPLAY, OUTWITS, OUTRANK, OUTGREW, OUTSELL. If you hold O+U+T, check for 4-letter verbs about surpassing. Common and memorable.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Combine prefix + suffix:</span> RE+DO+ING = REDOING. UN+PACK+S = UNPACKS. MIS+LEAD+S = MISLEADS. When your rack has both patterns, try layering them around a short root.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Use board tiles for longer prefixes:</span> OVER- and UNDER- use 4-5 rack tiles. But if part of the word already exists on the board, you can build through it. Existing DUE + your OVER tiles = OVERDUE bingo.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/common-bingo-endings" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Common Bingo Endings — Suffixes That Win</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/how-to-spot-bingos-faster" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">How to Spot Bingos Faster in Scrabble</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/hooking-existing-words" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Hooking Existing Words — Scrabble Strategy</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Try our free Scrabble Word Finder — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
